{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7134993f-bee3-4d0d-aed5-307814422af1","content":"No files found — this is an empty directory, so I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings. Here's the pattern:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\"\n                   VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n## Key changes\n\n1. **`xmlns:vm`** — import the namespace containing your ViewModel.\n2. **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — this is the single line that enables compiled bindings for the entire page. The compiler resolves every `{Binding ...}` against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings give you **build-time validation by default** — if you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you get a **compiler error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo go further, add this to your `.csproj` to **treat binding warnings as errors**:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Existing properties... -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the MAUI/Xamarin diagnostic for binding issues. This promotes them to build-breaking errors.\n\n## When you need to opt out\n\nIf a section binds to a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`), set `x:DataType` locally. To fall back to classic bindings for one element, use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"`:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicThing}\" x:DataType=\"x:Null\" />\n```\n\n**Summary:** Add `x:DataType` → bindings are compiled → typos and type mismatches become compiler errors instead of silent runtime failures.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"95ddaad8-21b4-4c9f-9f6f-20aeccee8c07","outputTokens":760,"requestId":"D44A:298C73:1D7ABEE:21061B9:6A07C0F0"},"id":"ea8e34b5-b255-4b25-beaf-189897c87b5d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:57:35.039Z","parentId":"98f34e4d-51a2-43cf-9f14-edc1faf40710"}
